text:
Guys, some of you mentioned that you donâ€™t see the slots on CoWin even though you acted immediately on the alert. I can understand the frustration. Right now, there is a huge supply-demand mismatch, especially for Bengaluru and Mumbai. Consider this, there are over 6000 people just here in this group fighting for 66 slots. You know how that will end.
Some of you have been successful (especially around that 2:34pm alert) when 1500 slots were opened and reached out to me to tell about it over Twitter. In case anyone has found any trick/ suggestion on how we can book the slot on CoWin faster or anything else, please let me know and I can share it in this group.
From my side, I would want to try and help too. Yesterday I made the script run checks every minute. Tomorrow onwards I am planning to run it every 10sec, around that 10:30am-6:30pm mark when slots seem to be getting added to CoWin. I am not saying that will solve all the issues. But should give you a better chance.
Stay safe!
(Twitter)

Hi guys, couple of things to share:
1. There is twitter thread I had put up for some good (success?) practices based on inputs from different subscribers of these channels who have successfully booked using these alerts. You can read and add on to them:

This channel now has over 18k subscribers and I am not sure if that is a factor. To test this I am going to post a message here exactly at 10:15pm. Let me know when you are receiving it and if there is any delay. Please reply only on the below thread:

Thank you.
Stay safe!

Hi guys, there is an important announcement to share.
There has been some changes in the CoWIN API limits overnight and hence it is getting increasingly difficult to maintain this level of alerts. And Bengaluru requires really fast updates. 
While we have this channel, I have come across another programmer, based out of Bangalore, who is doing the same process, which is updating faster than what we had, but that was over Twitter (

). We share a common goal of helping people get access to vaccines even when they are not very comfortable with technology and hence decided to team up instead of doing the same thing separately. From now on, the updates will come from him on this Channel. For any queries, please reach out to him (

). For now he will be known only by this handle (even I do not know his name!). When the time is right, he will reveal his identity and make sure that you thank him for his service. 
I am planning to use my resources to reach out to smaller districts that have been requesting similar alert mechanisms. 
It has been a pleasure serving you.
God bless & stay safe!
